        "content": "<p>afonso360 opened <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/3164\">PR #3164</a> from <code>interpreter-stack</code> to <code>main</code>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>With this PR we also change the approach for heap loads and stores.</p>\n<p>Previously we would use the offset as the address to the heap. However, this approach does not allow using the <code>load</code>/<code>store</code> instructions to read/write from both the heap and the stack.</p>\n<p>We now return the real addresses from the addressing instructions (<code>stack_addr</code>/<code>heap_addr</code>), and instead check if the address passed into the <code>load</code>/<code>store</code> instructions points to an area in the heap or the stack.</p>\n</blockquote>",
